          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Important:</strong> While the federal deadline is June 30, 2026, applying this late will cause you to miss most state aid and many institutional scholarships.
            Aim to submit your FAFSA as close to October 1 as possible.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Quick State Summary -->
      <section class="box-rounded mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-blue mb-4">State Deadline Overview</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="text-center p-4 bg-red-50 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-red-600">{urgentDeadlines.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-red-800">States with Jan/Feb Deadlines</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-amber-600">{springDeadlines.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-amber-800">States with Mar-May Deadlines</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-600">{noDeadline.length}</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-700">"Apply ASAP" or No Deadline</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Many states award aid on a first-come, first-served basis until funds are exhausted. Even states without formal deadlines strongly encourage early application.
        </p>
      </section>

